Her husband Ronald, a sugarfield labourer from Guyana, West Indies, was in 1991 declared legally insane. This mental illness had set in about 16 years prior to his diagnosis which his family even by then had known.

Joy stayed in the marriage for about 15 years before deciding she had had enough of the abnormal behavior that has ultimately contributed to the deterioration in her health. Little by little she had fallen into depression as a direct result of her 0-124 selfless love and support of Ronald during his ''Awakening of the Chariot of the Sun Beams''.

Within these three weeks she lost an astounding 60 lbs. She could never sleep knowing her husband was going through another episode, cycle or phase of schizophrenic behavior. At times she would find herself praying for the spirit of the Lord to ease her mind, body and soul. The close to dead feeling she had experienced; was knowing that her husband could soon turn violent as she had experienced in the past.

"I don't know how you managed to stay with him for so long," Joy sister Christmas said. Joy was crying after finding out her husband had been permanently committed. She was now left homeless after bringing him home from Lusignan Diaconal home where he had done his physiotherapy;
